def count_black_cells(n: int) -> int:
    """
    Calculate the number of black cells in an n x n chessboard.

    Parameters:
    n (int): The size of the chessboard (n x n).

    Returns:
    int: The number of black cells in the chessboard.
    """
    return pow(n, 2) / 2
